folder: Bedford Avenue & Division Avenue, Brooklyn, NY
text:
Bedford Ave., west side, at Division Ave. The fountain was installed in 1869. The present fountain replaced the original in 1878.

About 1890?

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

folder: Bedford Avenue & Division Avenue, Brooklyn, NY
text:
Bedford Ave., south from Division Avenue. At the left, is seen Christ Episcopal Church. (Protestant).
About 1900?
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

folder: Division Avenue & Bedford Avenue, Brooklyn, NY
text:
Division Ave., south side, east from Bedford Ave., showing at the right the Partridge Memorial Chapel belonging to the Christ Church
Protestant Episcopal.)
1922.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

folder: Bedford Avenue & Division Avenue, Brooklyn, NY
text:
Bedford Avenue, east from Division Avenue. View 1 shows only the north side of the avenue with the Christ Protestant Episcopal Church and the First Dutch Reformed Church (background) of Williamsburg.
View 2 shows the Christ Church and View 3 both sides of the avenue and the small square at the intersection of Bedford and Division.
Eugene L. Armbruster, Collection
Views 1,2: 1924
View 3: 1929
